Scripts to automate development tasks

- Upgrade

Goal: Upgrade Jhipster to version specified in the project.json
Run: gradlew -q upgrade

Note: Please backup your application before running this command.

To get a report first:

Run: gradlew -q upgrade -Pdryrun

A file or directory can be upgraded by various actions
	- delete (delete the file or folder)
	- replace (replace the file or folder by the one of the new Jhipster version)
	- skip (no action, but report this in the output)
	- ignore (no action)


- Resources

Goal: Create a list of resources in a Jhipster project. This list can be used in a projectfile
Run: gradlew -q resources

- Version

Goal: Update the version for the listed files in versioned_files.json
Run: gradlew -q version


